<note id="fs-id1168343131452" class="try">
<exercise id="fs-id1168344192020">
<problem id="fs-id1168344509721">
<para id="fs-id1168344502381">Solve: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>18</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1168344215124">
<para id="fs-id1168344315440"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>−5</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</solution>
</exercise>
</note>
<note id="fs-id1168343063658" class="try">
<exercise id="fs-id1168344298356">
<problem id="fs-id1168344302388">
<para id="fs-id1168344322609">Solve: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>k</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn><m:mi>k</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>17</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1168344441119">
<para id="fs-id1168343187217"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>k</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>−6</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</solution>
</exercise>
</note>
<para id="fs-id1168344334583">In the last example, we could have made the left side the “variable” side, but it would have led to a negative coefficient on the variable term. (Try it!) While we could work with the negative, there is less chance of errors when working with positives. The strategy outlined above helps avoid the negatives!</para>
<para id="fs-id1168344297464">To solve an equation with fractions, we just follow the steps of our strategy to get the solution!</para>
<example id="fs-id1168344286844">
<exercise id="fs-id1168344108706"><problem id="fs-id1168342992147">
<para id="fs-id1168344250068">Solve: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mfrac><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
