<section id="fs-id1168344334793" class="key-concepts">
<title>Key Concepts</title>
<list id="fs-id1168343048626" list-type="bulleted" bullet-style="bullet">
<item><emphasis effect="bold">Beginning Strategy for Solving an Equation with Variables and Constants on Both Sides of the Equation</emphasis>
<list id="fs-id1168343052761" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" class="stepwise">
<item>Choose which side will be the “variable” side—the other side will be the “constant” side.</item>
<item>Collect the variable terms to the “variable” side of the equation, using the Addition or Subtraction Property of Equality.</item>
<item>Collect all the constants to the other side of the equation, using the Addition or Subtraction Property of Equality.</item>
<item>Make the coefficient of the variable equal 1, using the Multiplication or Division Property of Equality.</item>
<item>Check the solution by substituting it into the original equation.</item>
</list></item>
</list>
</section>
